df = fread("/home/aishwarya/Documents/Academia/Sem 5/DA/DA19_A2_Datasets/dataset/tweets_kabir_singh.csv")
df <- select(df, author, text)
get_sentiments("afinn")
get_sentiments("nrc")
get_sentiments("bing")
# tokenize
tokens <- tibble(text = df$text) %>% unnest_tokens(word, text)
tokens %>%
  inner_join(get_sentiments("nrc")) %>% # pull out only sentiment words
  count(sentiment) %>% # count the # of positive & negative words
  spread(sentiment, n, fill = 0) %>% # made data wide rather than narrow
  mutate(sentiment = positive - negative) # # of positive words - # of negative owrds
## Joining, by = "word"
## # A tibble: 1 x 11
##   anger anticipation disgust  fear   joy negative positive sadness surprise
##   <dbl>        <dbl>   <dbl> <dbl> <dbl>    <dbl>    <dbl>   <dbl>    <dbl>
## 1  2836         6540    2120  3641  6285     5164    11327    2433     2566
## # … with 2 more variables: trust <dbl>, sentiment <dbl>
kabir_singh_sentiment <- tokens %>%
  inner_join(get_sentiments("bing")) %>% # pull out only sentiment words
  count(sentiment) %>% # count the # of positive & negative words
  spread(sentiment, n, fill = 0) %>% # made data wide rather than narrow
  mutate(sentiment = positive - negative) # # of positive words - # of negative owrds
## Joining, by = "word"

#ggplot(kabir_singh_sentiment, aes(x=sentiment))
bing_word_counts <- tokens %>%
  inner_join(get_sentiments("bing")) %>%
  count(word, sentiment, sort = TRUE) %>%
  ungroup()
## Joining, by = "word"
bing_word_counts
## # A tibble: 1,540 x 3
##    word    sentiment     n
##    <chr>   <chr>     <int>
##  1 love    positive    912
##  2 like    positive    844
##  3 best    positive    819
##  4 good    positive    529
##  5 loved   positive    385
##  6 awesome positive    333
##  7 great   positive    313
##  8 amazing positive    299
##  9 well    positive    247
## 10 toxic   negative    216
## # … with 1,530 more rows
bing_word_counts %>%
  group_by(sentiment) %>%
  top_n(10) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  mutate(word = reorder(word, n)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(word, n, fill = sentiment)) +
  geom_col(show.legend = FALSE) +
  facet_wrap(~sentiment, scales = "free_y") +
  labs(y = "Contribution to sentiment",
       x = NULL) +
  coord_flip()
## Selecting by n

tokens %>%
  anti_join(stop_words) %>%
  count(word) %>%
  with(wordcloud(word, n, max.words = 100))
## Joining, by = "word"

tokens %>%
  inner_join(get_sentiments("bing")) %>%
  count(word, sentiment, sort = TRUE) %>%
  acast(word ~ sentiment, value.var = "n", fill = 0) %>%
  comparison.cloud(colors = c("red", "cornflowerblue"),
                   max.words = 100)
